26 PART VI. REVISIONS TO LAWS GOVERNING PEER-TO-PEER VEHICLE
27 SHARING
28 SECTION 6.(a) Article 10B of Chapter 20 of the General Statutes reads as rewritten:
29 "Article 10B.
30 "Peer-to-Peer Vehicle Sharing.
31 "§ 20-280.15. Definitions.
32 The following definitions apply in this Article:
33 (1) Airport operator. – As defined in G.S. 20-280.1.
34 (2) Peer-to-peer vehicle sharing. – The authorized use of a shared vehicle for
35 financial consideration by an individual other than the shared vehicle owner
36 through a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
37 (3) Peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program. – A business platform that connects
38 shared vehicle owners with drivers to enable the sharing of vehicles for
39 financial consideration.peer-to-peer vehicle sharing.
40 (4) Shared vehicle. – A vehicle that is available for sharing through a peer-to-peer
41 vehicle sharing program.sharing.
42 (4a) Shared vehicle delivery period. – The period of time during which a shared
43 vehicle is being delivered to the location of the vehicle sharing start time, if
44 applicable, as documented by the governing vehicle sharing agreement.
45 (4b) Shared vehicle driver. – An individual who is authorized to drive the shared
46 vehicle by the shared vehicle owner under a vehicle sharing agreement.
47 (5) Shared vehicle owner. – The registered owner of a shared vehicle that is made
48 available for sharing through a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.vehicle,
49 or a person or entity designated by the registered owner, who has not made an
50 election under G.S. 105-187.5.
