General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (5a) Vehicle sharing agreement. – The terms and conditions applicable to a shared
2 vehicle owner and a shared vehicle driver that govern the use of that shared
3 vehicle through a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
4 (5b) Vehicle sharing period. – The period of time that commences with the shared
5 vehicle delivery period, or if there is no shared vehicle delivery period, the
6 vehicle sharing start time, and in either case ends at the vehicle sharing
7 termination time.
8 (6) Vehicle sharing provider. – The person or entity that operates, facilitates, or
9 administers the provision of personal vehicle sharing through a peer-to-peer
10 vehicle sharing program.
11 (7) Vehicle sharing start time. – The time when a shared vehicle becomes subject
12 to the control of a shared vehicle driver at or after the time the reservation of
13 a shared vehicle is scheduled to begin as documented in the records of a
14 peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
15 (8) Vehicle sharing termination time. – The earliest occurrence of any of the
16 following events:
17 a. The expiration of the agreed upon period of time established for the
18 use of a shared vehicle according to the terms of the vehicle sharing
19 agreement if the shared vehicle is delivered to the location agreed upon
20 in the vehicle sharing agreement.
21 b. When the shared vehicle is returned to an alternate location agreed
22 upon by the shared vehicle owner and shared vehicle driver as
23 communicated through a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program, which
24 alternate location shall be incorporated into the vehicle sharing
25 agreement.
26 c. When the shared vehicle owner, or the shared vehicle owner's
27 authorized designee, takes possession and control of the shared
28 vehicle.
29 "§ 20-280.19. Assumption of liability; exceptions.
30 (a) Amount and Manner of Assumption of Liability. – Except as otherwise provided in
31 subsection (b) of this section, a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program shall assume the liability
32 of a shared vehicle owner during the vehicle sharing period for any of the following:
33 (1) Bodily injury or property damage to third parties.
34 (2) Uninsured and underinsured motorist losses.
35 (3) Personal injury protection losses.
36 The liability shall be to the extent personal injury protection is required by law in an amount
37 stated in the vehicle sharing agreement. The liability amount shall not be less than that required
38 by G.S. 20-279.21(b)(2) and G.S. 20-279.21(b)(3) and the manner of the assumption of liability
39 shall also be the same as required by those statutes.
40 (b) Exceptions. – The assumption of liability under subsection (a) of this section does not
41 apply if any of the following apply:
42 (1) A shared vehicle owner makes an intentional or fraudulent material
43 misrepresentation or omission to the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program
44 before the vehicle sharing period in which the loss occurred.
45 (2) A shared vehicle driver, acting in concert with a shared vehicle owner, fails to
46 return the shared vehicle pursuant to the terms of the vehicle sharing
47 agreement.
48 "§ 20-280.21. Insurance coverage.
49 (a) Insurance Coverage of Shared Vehicle. – A peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program
50 shall ensure that during each vehicle sharing period, both the shared vehicle owner and the shared
51 vehicle driver are each insured under a motor vehicle liability insurance policy that provides
Page 4 House Bill 356-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 insurance coverage in amounts no less than the minimum amounts set forth in
2 G.S. 20-279.21(b)(2) and G.S. 20-279.21(b)(3). The motor vehicle liability insurance policy
3 shall also do one of the following:
4 (1) Acknowledge that the shared vehicle insured under the motor vehicle liability
5 insurance policy is made available and used in a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing
6 program.
7 (2) Not exclude the use of a shared vehicle in a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing
8 program by a shared vehicle driver.
9 (b) Maintenance of Insurance Coverage of Shared Vehicle. – The required motor vehicle
10 liability insurance policy shall be maintained by at least one of the following:
11 (1) The shared vehicle owner.
12 (2) The shared vehicle driver.
13 (3) The peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
14 (c) Insurance Coverage Differences. – The motor vehicle liability insurance policy
15 required under this section shall be the primary motor vehicle liability insurance policy during
16 each vehicle sharing period. If a claim occurs in another state with minimum financial
17 responsibility limits higher than those required by G.S. 20-279.21(b)(2) and
18 G.S. 20-279.21(b)(3) during the vehicle sharing period, the motor vehicle liability insurance
19 policy required by this section shall satisfy the difference in minimum coverage amounts, up to
20 the applicable policy limits.
21 (d) Assumption of Primary Liability. – The entity or entities maintaining the motor
22 vehicle liability insurance policy shall assume primary liability for a claim when any of the
23 following occur:
24 (1) A dispute exists as to who controlled the shared vehicle at the time of the loss
25 and the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program does not have available, did not
26 retain, or fails to provide the information required by G.S. 20-280.25.
27 (2) A dispute exists as to whether the shared vehicle was returned to the alternate
28 location agreed upon by the shared vehicle owner and shared vehicle driver
29 and incorporated into the vehicle sharing agreement.
30 (e) Lapsed or Inadequate Insurance Coverage. – If the motor vehicle liability insurance
31 policy maintained by a shared vehicle owner or shared vehicle driver has lapsed or does not
32 provide the required coverage, the motor vehicle liability insurance policy maintained by a
33 peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program shall provide the required coverage beginning with the first
34 dollar of a claim and have the duty to defend that claim, except under the exceptions set forth in
35 G.S. 20-280.19(b).
36 (f) No Dependence on Another Insurance Policy. – Coverage under a motor vehicle
37 liability insurance policy maintained by the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program shall not be
38 dependent on another automobile insurer first denying a claim nor shall another motor vehicle
39 liability insurance policy be required to first deny a claim.
40 "§ 20-280.23. No limitations on liability; indemnification.
41 No Limitations or Restrictions on Liability of Peer-to-Peer Vehicle Sharing Program;
42 Indemnification. – Nothing in this Article shall be interpreted as either limiting or restricting any
43 of the following:
44 (1) The liability of the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program for any act or
45 omission of the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program itself that results in
46 injury to any person as a result of the use of a shared vehicle through a
47 peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
48 (2) The ability of the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program to, by contract, seek
49 indemnification from the shared vehicle owner or the shared vehicle driver for
50 economic loss sustained by the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program resulting
51 from a breach of the terms and conditions of the vehicle sharing agreement.
