1 "§ 20-280.25. Notification of implications of lien on shared vehicle.
2 At the time when a vehicle owner registers as a shared vehicle owner on a peer-to-peer vehicle
3 sharing program and prior to the time when the shared vehicle owner makes a shared vehicle
4 available for sharing on the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program, the peer-to-peer vehicle
5 sharing program shall notify the shared vehicle owner that if the shared vehicle has a lien against
6 it, the use of the shared vehicle through the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program, including use
7 without physical damage coverage, may violate the terms of the contract with the lienholder.
8 "§ 20-280.27. Exclusions for personal motor vehicle liability insurance policies.
9 (a) A motor vehicle insurer that writes motor vehicle liability insurance policies in this
10 State may exclude any and all coverage and the duty to defend or indemnify for any claim arising
11 out of peer-to-peer vehicle sharing that is covered under a shared vehicle owner's motor vehicle
12 liability insurance policy for any of the following:
13 (1) Liability coverage for bodily injury and property damage.
14 (2) Personal injury protection coverage.
15 (3) Uninsured and underinsured motorist coverage.
16 (4) Medical payments coverage.
17 (5) Comprehensive physical damage coverage.
18 (6) Collision physical damage coverage.
19 (b) Nothing in this Article shall be interpreted or construed as invalidating or limiting an
20 exclusion contained in a motor vehicle liability insurance policy, including any insurance policy
21 in use or approved for use that excludes coverage for motor vehicles made available for rent,
22 sharing, or hire or for any business use.
23 (c) Nothing in this Article shall be interpreted or construed as invalidating, limiting, or
24 restricting a motor vehicle insurer's ability to underwrite any insurance policy.
25 (d) Nothing in this Article shall be interpreted or construed as invalidating, limiting, or
26 restricting a motor vehicle insurer's ability to cancel and nonrenew policies, including for
27 participation in a peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program.
28 "§ 20-280.29. Record keeping.
29 (a) A peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program shall collect and verify records pertaining to
30 the use of the shared vehicle. The records shall include vehicle sharing times used, vehicle
31 sharing period pickup and drop-off locations, fees paid by the shared vehicle driver, and revenues
32 received by the shared vehicle owner. Upon request, this information shall be provided to the
33 shared vehicle driver, the shared vehicle owner, the shared vehicle owner's insurer, and the shared
34 vehicle driver's insurer for claim coverage investigation, settlement, negotiation, or litigation.
35 (b) The peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program shall retain all records required under this
36 section for a time period not less than the applicable personal injury statute of limitations.
37 "§ 20-280.31. Vicarious liability.
38 A peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program and a shared vehicle owner shall be exempt from
39 vicarious liability consistent with 49 U.S.C. § 30106 and under any state or local law that imposes
40 liability solely based on vehicle ownership.
41 "§ 20-280.33. Contribution against indemnification.
42 A motor vehicle insurer that defends or indemnifies a claim involving a shared vehicle that
43 is excluded under the terms of its policy shall have the right to seek contribution against the motor
44 vehicle insurer of the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program if the claim meets all of the following
45 conditions:
46 (1) The claim is made against the shared vehicle owner or the shared vehicle
47 driver for loss or injury that occurs during the vehicle sharing period.
48 (2) The claim is excluded under the terms of its policy.
49 "§ 20-280.35. Insurable interest.
