14 "§ 20-280.37. Consumer protections for peer-to-peer vehicle sharing programs.
15 Each vehicle sharing agreement made in this State shall disclose to the shared vehicle owner
16 and the shared vehicle driver, at a minimum, all of the following:
17 (1) Any right of the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program to seek indemnification
18 from the shared vehicle owner or the shared vehicle driver for economic loss
19 sustained by the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program resulting from a breach
20 of the terms and conditions of the vehicle sharing agreement.
21 (2) That a motor vehicle liability insurance policy issued to the shared vehicle
22 owner for the shared vehicle or to the shared vehicle driver does not provide
23 a defense or indemnification for any claim asserted by the peer-to-peer vehicle
24 sharing program.
25 (3) That the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program's insurance coverage on the
26 shared vehicle owner and the shared vehicle driver is in effect only during
27 each vehicle sharing period and that the shared vehicle driver and the shared
28 vehicle owner may not have insurance coverage for any use of the shared
29 vehicle by the shared vehicle driver after the vehicle sharing termination time.
30 (4) The daily rate, fees, and, if applicable, any insurance or protection package
31 costs that are charged to the shared vehicle owner or the shared vehicle driver.
32 (5) The shared vehicle owner's motor vehicle liability insurance may not provide
33 coverage for a shared vehicle.
34 (6) An emergency telephone number to personnel capable of fielding roadside
35 assistance and other customer service inquiries.
36 (7) Any conditions under which a shared vehicle driver must maintain a motor
37 vehicle liability insurance policy with certain applicable coverage limits on a
38 primary basis in order to book a shared motor vehicle.
39 "§ 20-280.39. Drivers license verification and data retention.
40 (a) A peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program may not enter into a peer-to-peer vehicle
41 sharing program agreement with a shared vehicle driver unless the shared vehicle driver who will
42 operate the shared vehicle meets one of the following requirements:
43 (1) Has a valid drivers license issued pursuant to G.S. 20-7 that authorizes the
44 driver to operate a motor vehicle of the class of the shared vehicle.
45 (2) Is a nonresident of this State who meets all of the following requirements:
46 a. Has a valid drivers license issued by the state or country of the driver's
47 residence that authorizes the driver in that state or country to drive a
48 motor vehicle of the class of the shared vehicle.
49 b. Is at least the same age as that required of a resident of this State to
50 operate a motor vehicle of the class of the shared vehicle.
