9 "§ 20-280.41. Responsibility for equipment of a shared vehicle.
10 A peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program shall have sole responsibility for any equipment, such
11 as a global positioning system (GPS) or other special equipment that is put in or on the vehicle
12 to monitor or facilitate the vehicle sharing transaction, and shall agree to indemnify and hold
13 harmless the shared vehicle owner for any damage to or theft of such equipment during the
14 vehicle sharing period not caused by the shared vehicle owner. The peer-to-peer vehicle sharing
15 program shall have the right to seek indemnity from the shared vehicle driver for any loss or
16 damage to such equipment that occurs during the vehicle sharing period.
17 "§ 20-280.43. Automobile safety recalls.
18 (a) At the time when a vehicle owner registers as a shared vehicle owner on a peer-to-peer
19 vehicle sharing program and prior to the time when the shared vehicle owner makes a shared
20 vehicle available for sharing on the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program, the peer-to-peer
21 vehicle sharing program shall do all of the following:
22 (1) Verify that the shared vehicle does not have any safety recalls on the vehicle
23 for which the repairs have not been made.
24 (2) Notify the shared vehicle owner of the requirements of this section.
25 (b) If the shared vehicle owner has received actual notice of a safety recall on the shared
26 vehicle, the shared vehicle owner shall do the following:
27 (1) Refrain from making a vehicle available as a shared vehicle on a peer-to-peer
28 vehicle sharing program until the safety recall repair has been made.
29 (2) Remove the shared vehicle as available on the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing
30 program as soon as practicable after receiving the notice of the safety recall
31 and until the safety recall repair has been made.
32 (3) Notify the peer-to-peer vehicle sharing program about the safety recall so that
33 the shared vehicle owner may address the safety recall repair as soon as
34 practicable."
35 SECTION 6.(b) This section becomes effective October 1, 2026, and applies to all
36 peer-to-peer vehicle sharing agreements entered into on or after that date.
